                            <comment id="16020401" author="pnpritchard" created="Mon, 22 May 2017 23:37:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Screen shot of JVisualVM thread visualization.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16020953" author="srowen" created="Tue, 23 May 2017 09:38:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CC &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=viirya&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;viirya&quot;&gt;viirya&lt;/a&gt;  for &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/16474/files#diff-ee26d4c4be21e92e92a02e9f16dbc285R559&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/16474/files#diff-ee26d4c4be21e92e92a02e9f16dbc285R559&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;br/&gt;
It does look like this is missing a &lt;tt&gt;shutdown()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16020966" author="viirya" created="Tue, 23 May 2017 09:50:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am looking up this. Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sowen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sowen&quot;&gt;sowen&lt;/a&gt; for pinging me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16021166" author="viirya" created="Tue, 23 May 2017 13:07:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems to me that to share the task support between parquet file reading is better than shutdowning after each reading?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16021186" author="srowen" created="Tue, 23 May 2017 13:30:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, possibly. The main tradeoff is that concurrent read jobs share a pool of threads, and don&apos;t get their own. You don&apos;t need to spin up new threads, but also, will have a thread pool lying around for the whole app lifetime. No big deal. The main question is whether concurrent jobs were intended to limit their total concurrency on purpose by sharing a pool or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16021236" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 23 May 2017 14:12:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;viirya&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/18073&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/18073&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16021237" author="viirya" created="Tue, 23 May 2017 14:12:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok. It seems better not to change the concurrency, I add a shutdown and a test case for it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16023863" author="apachespark" created="Wed, 24 May 2017 23:18:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;viirya&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
